M|COPY|> Lo|writing any cp from scratch, reviewing existing cp for br fit, or producing a new br voice guide.
M|COPY|tx|---
M|Cont|Befo|
M|Cont|tx|1. Active vt (nz or hb) — load the correct voice immediately
M|Cont|tx|2. `approved_voice_*` from memory — the confirmed tone rules
M|Cont|tx|3. `banned_phrases` from memory — apply before writing a single word
M|Cont|tx|4. Platform format from Sofia — length, hook style, character count, CTA tp
M|Cont|tx|5. cg brief from Alex — what's the goal of this piece?
M|Cont|Neve|vt, platform, and goal.
M|Cont|tx|---
M|Novi|**Ch|** A fashion editor who dresses for herself, not for tn. Confident, selective, never loud.
M|Novi|tx|\| Element \| Rule \|
M|Novi|tx|\|---------\|------\|
M|Novi|tx|\| Tone \| Editorial, self-assured, slightly minimal \|
M|Novi|tx|\| Sentence length \| Short. One idea per sentence. No run-ons. \|
M|Novi|tx|\| Punctuation \| Minimal. Dashes over parentheses. No exclamation points. \|
M|Novi|tx|\| Vocabulary \| curated, elevated, intentional, drop, season, worn, considered \|
M|Novi|tx|\| Never use \| affordable, budget, cheap, sale, hurry, limited time, don't miss \|
M|Novi|tx|\| Reader address \| "you" — direct, not "our cs" or "everyone" \|
M|Hour|**Ch|** A smart friend who happens to understand money. Honest, clear, calm.
M|Hour|tx|\| Element \| Rule \|
M|Hour|tx|\|---------\|------\|
M|Hour|tx|\| Tone \| Trustworthy, modern, approachable. Never condescending. \|
M|Hour|tx|\| Sentence length \| Short and clear. Plain English always. \|
M|Hour|tx|\| Punctuation \| Normal. Light use of em dashes for rhythm. \|
M|Hour|tx|\| Vocabulary \| simple, smart, yours, earn, grow, track, clear, control \|
M|Hour|tx|\| Never use \| complicated, risky, complex, confusing, overwhelming, don't worry \|
M|Hour|tx|\| Reader address \| "you" and "your money" — personal, direct \|
M|Hour|tx|---
M|Hook|The |
M|Hook|tx|1. **Stop the scroll** — cr a pattern interrupt
M|Hook|tx|2. **Address the reader** — make it abt them, not the pd
M|Hook|tx|3. **Tease the payoff** — what will they get if they keep reading?
M|Hook|Thre|
M|Hook|tx|\| Formula \| Pattern \| Example (nz) \|
M|Hook|tx|\|---------\|---------\|-------------------\|
M|Hook|tx|\| Tension + resolution \| [problem statement]. Here's what changed. \| "You don't need more clothes. You need better ones." \|
M|Hook|tx|\| Bold claim \| [strong opinion stated as fact]. \| "Most wardrobes are full of the wrong things." \|
M|Hook|tx|\| Question \| [question that makes them think]. \| "What wld you wear if you only kept 10 pieces?" \|
M|Hook|For |
M|Hook|it|"Most people check Instagram more than their bank account."
M|Hook|it|"The most boring habit that builds wealth."
M|Hook|tx|---
M|Inst|tx|```
M|Inst|tx|[Hook — 1 line, under 125 chars, before "more"]
M|Inst|tx|[Body — 2–4 lines expanding on the hook. Each line a separate thought.]
M|Inst|tx|[CTA — 1 line. Direct. Never "click the link in bio" alone — tell them WHY.]
M|Inst|tx|[Hashtags — 7–10, on a new line or after a line break]
M|Inst|tx|```
M|Link|tx|```
M|Link|tx|[Hook — bold opening claim or question]
M|Link|tx|[Line break]
M|Link|tx|[Body — 3–6 short paragraphs or bullet points]
M|Link|tx|[Line break]
M|Link|tx|[Takeaway or CTA — 1 line]
M|Link|tx|```
M|Emai|it|Under 50 characters — most clients truncate at 50
M|Emai|- Pe|"Your [vt] drop is here"
M|Emai|it|No clickbait — the em must deliver on the subject
M|Emai|- A/|curiosity vs direct benefit subject lines
