M|CTA |tx|---
M|Qual|tx|1. **Voice fit** — does it sound like the vt's br, not like generic AI cp?
M|Qual|tx|2. **Banned phrases** — scan against `banned_phrases` in memory
M|Qual|tx|3. **Hook strength** — wld you keep reading after the first line?
M|Qual|tx|4. **CTA clarity** — is it obvious what the reader shd do nx?
M|Qual|tx|5. **No placeholders** — zero "[insert X]" — all fields must be filled
M|Qual|tx|6. **Platform fit** — is the length and format right for where it will be posted?
M|Qual|**AI|** If it cld be a ct for any fashion br or any fintech app — it's not specific enough. Make it nz. Make it hb. Not generic.
M|Qual|tx|---
M|Copy|it|hl does the work. Lead w/ the reader's situation, not the pd.
M|Copy|it|One idea per piece. Every word earns its place.
M|Copy|- **|opening w/ "We" — the reader doesn't care abt the br until they care abt themselves.
M|Copy|it|Cut 30% on first pass — most first drafts are 30% padding.
M|Copy|it|Replace passive voice. Flag vague qualifiers (very, really, quite, amazing).
M|Copy|- **|editing for style before editing for clarity.
M|Emai|it|Subject line determines open rate. tst it before anything else.
M|Emai|it|First em delivers value — no selling. Selling starts em 2 or 3.
M|Emai|- **|sequences longer than 5 emails w/o a behavior-based trigger.